faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] As someone who battles daily with makeup, sunscreen, and the general grime of life, finding a cleansing oil that truly works without leaving my skin feeling stripped or greasy has been a quest. Enter the Ma:nyo Pure Cleansing Oil, and let me tell you, my search might just be over.
From the first pump, I was impressed by its lightweight texture. Unlike some thicker oils that feel heavy and almost sticky, this one glides effortlessly onto dry skin. The instructions recommend massaging it in for a bit, and I found myself actually enjoying the process ‚Äì it feels luxurious and allows the oil to really dissolve everything sitting on my face.
And dissolve it does! This oil is a powerhouse when it comes to deep cleaning. Foundation, waterproof mascara, even that stubborn liquid eyeliner I swear is cemented on ‚Äì all melted away with surprising ease. It literally melts away eye makeup, dirt, and excess sebum to keep my skin clean and refreshed. This is especially fantastic after a long day when all you want to do is effortlessly remove your makeup and feel clean.
What truly sets this product apart, however, are its double cleansing properties. I'm a firm believer in the two-step cleanse, and this oil eliminates the need for a separate water-based cleanser to follow. Once you add a little water, it emulsifies beautifully into a milky lather, rinsing away cleanly without any residue. My skin feels incredibly soft, thoroughly clean, and surprisingly hydrated, never tight or dry. Plus, it has a pleasant smell that adds to the overall enjoyable experience without being overwhelming.
I've been using this cleansing oil for a few weeks now, and I've noticed a significant improvement in the overall clarity and texture of my skin. My pores seem less congested, and I haven't experienced any breakouts, which can sometimes be a concern with oil-based cleansers if they don't rinse off properly.
Pros:
 * Truly lightweight: No heavy, greasy feeling.
 * Exceptional deep clean: Effectively removes all traces of makeup and impurities, including stubborn eye makeup, dirt, and excess sebum.
 * Excellent double cleansing properties: Emulsifies perfectly and rinses clean.
 * Leaves skin soft and hydrated: No tightness or dryness; keeps skin clean and refreshed.
 * Gentle yet effective: Suitable for daily use.
 * Pleasant smell: Adds to the enjoyable cleansing experience.
 * Great for end-of-day makeup removal: Quickly takes off makeup after a long day.
Cons:
 * Honestly, I'm struggling to find one!
Overall Impression:
The Manual Pure Cleansing Oil is a game-changer for anyone seeking an efficient, effective, and enjoyable cleansing experience. It simplifies my routine without compromising on results, delivering a deep clean that leaves my skin feeling balanced and refreshed. The added bonus of its pleasant scent and ability to thoroughly remove all traces of makeup, especially after a long day, makes it a true staple in my skincare routine. I highly recommend giving this a try ‚Äì your skin will thank you!
faceoff_positive.headline: Great product with a surprisingly pleasing scent!

faceoff_negative.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] What I love about this oil cleanser is that it really gets deep down in your pores to get the make up and sweat that gets packed in from a full day. After a full wash and then hitting my t zone again it was able to really get my face clean. I liked that there wasn't much of a scent. My only complaint is that it was a really drying formula for my skin. My fave was super peely after using and I had to use a lot of moisturizer to get my skin hydrated after using the cleanser. I have combination skin so I would recommend this cleanser to someone who is on the oilier side. But since it really got my make up off, I'll be using for nights that I slept in my make up and need a good deep clean in the morning combined with a heavy moisturizer.
faceoff_negative.headline: Squeaky clean but drying
